snippet: Voters turned out in big numbers after a controversy over a government plan to introduce mandatory pro-Beijing patriotic education in Hong Kong schools.
abstract: Pro-democracy candidates win strong voter support in legislative elections in Hong-Kong, but come away with fewer seats than expected; pro-Beijing political parties with greater financial resources and greater skill in navigating a complicated electoral system seem to have in part upended their prospects; pro-democracy groups appear to have narrowly retained at least one-third of the seats in the new Legislature, the proportion needed to block fundamental changes in the territory's law.
lead_paragraph: Voters turned out in big numbers after a controversy over a government plan to introduce mandatory pro-Beijing patriotic education in Hong Kong schools.

headline.seo: Hong Kong Voting for Legislature Is Heavy
headline.main: Pro-Beijing Candidates Outmaneuver Opponents as Hong Kong Votes
headline.print_headline: Pro-Beijing Candidates Outmaneuver Opponents in Hong Kong Elections
